snippet.textDisplay:
I was disappointed by the first. The expectations were set too high for a musical interpretation to meet the build up to the punchline.

I was underwhelmed by the second. It was a good punchline, but the build up of this bit was too much for a goofy accent and a semi-serious delivery to satisfy.

That ending, perfect. Floored. I wonder if the first two misses were planned, because it made the third "Jim Carrey crazy" straight man drama hit the perfect note for me! That was the raw emotion I needed for a satisfying conclusion to a massive build up for a punchline!
